HDMI KVM over IP Extender Kit&lt;/h2&gt;  &lt;p style='text-align: justify;'&gt;The Manhattan 1080p HDMI KVM over IP Extender Kit lets you access any computer (or other HDMI source) from a keyboard, mouse and display up to 120 m (394 ft.) away. You can either make a direct connection through a single RJ45 Ethernet cable (Cat6 or higher recommended for maximum range and performance) or you connect it to a switch in your existing network to overcome distance limitations.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style='text-align: justify;'&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Versatile Connectivity Options&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Use this HDMI over IP Extender with KVM function as a regular HDMI extender or as an HDMI KVM switch. As an extender, the HDMI and Ethernet ports can send up to &lt;a href='mailto:1080p@60Hz'&gt;1080p@60Hz&lt;/a&gt; (1920 × 1080) HDMI from your Blu-ray player, NVR/DVR, set-top box or game console to a remote display. There's an additional HDMI loop-out port on the transmitter so you can connect a display near the source for easier setup, while the IR feature lets you control the source remotely. As a full-control HDMI KVM switch, both modules also feature USB-A ports that connect your PC, laptop or MacBook to the transmitter and your keyboard/mouse to the receiver. Since the HDMI KVM extender is independent of your OS, you can use any computer you choose as your remote workstation. This flexibility makes it ideal for in-store POS (Point of Sale) systems and digital cash desks with touchscreens. Included in the package are four mounting brackets that let you tidily install its rugged metal housing on the wall or ceiling.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Controls a remote HDMI and USB-A equipped computer from a local display, keyboard and mouse&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Extends HDMI and USB signals up to 120 m (394 ft.) over a single Cat6 Ethernet Cable or to an unlimited range over an IP-enabled network&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Resolutions up to Full HD &lt;a href='mailto:1080p@60Hz'&gt;1080p@60Hz&lt;/a&gt; (1920 × 1080)&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Ideal for POS (Point of Sale) systems in stores or digital cash desks with touchscreens&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Reset button on both units to adjust signal to cable length&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Plug and play - requires no software installation or configuration&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;HDMI loop-out on transmitter to connect a display near the source for easier setup&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Supports 3D Video&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Works in existing network infrastructures via TCP/IP&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;EDID pass-through for automatic image optimization through configuration from your computer over your network&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Includes infrared (IR) blaster and receiver for remote control of the source device&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Supports MJPEG protocol for video compression&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Supports lossless LPCM 8 channel uncompressed audio formatting and 7.1 surround sound&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Rugged metal housing for maximum durability&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Includes mounting brackets for a tidy installation on wall or ceiling&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;HDMI, USB-A and Ethernet cables not included; available separately from Manhattan and Intellinet Network Solutions&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;For additional distance capabilities, use a 15 m (50 ft.) Manhattan High Speed HDMI Cable with Ethernet on both transmitter and receiver&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li style='text-align: justify;'&gt;Works independently of computer operating systems&lt;/li